WEBVTT

1
00:00:07.485 --> 00:00:10.097
Andre: <i>First. the
weather changed.</i>

2
00:00:10.271 --> 00:00:12.795
<i>In the final days of the Freeze.</i>

3
00:00:12.969 --> 00:00:15.667
<i>the visionary Mr. Wilford
prepared a Great Ark...</i>

4
00:00:15.798 --> 00:00:17.408
<i>Snowpiercer.</i>

5
00:00:17.626 --> 00:00:21.325
♪

6
00:00:21.456 --> 00:00:23.675
<i>There are places on the
Earth that are warming.</i>

7
00:00:23.806 --> 00:00:26.246
Woman: This train is all we've
known for the past eight years.

8
00:00:26.417 --> 00:00:28.698
Melanie on P.A.: Every passenger
will be allowed to choose

9
00:00:28.767 --> 00:00:33.033
between the train with me and
New Eden with Andre Layton.

10
00:00:33.207 --> 00:00:36.558
Woman: New Eden is our
chance at a fresh start.

11
00:00:36.732 --> 00:00:39.343
I will serve with you
till the end of the world.

12
00:00:39.517 --> 00:00:41.215
We could derail before
we even get there.

13
00:00:41.345 --> 00:00:42.694
It's good to take
a leap of faith.

14
00:00:42.781 --> 00:00:46.002
Man: Separating.

15
00:00:46.176 --> 00:00:49.223
- Goodbye. Javi.
<i>- Adios. amigo.</i>

16
00:00:49.310 --> 00:00:51.834
Andre: Those who choose New
Eden need to understand.

17
00:00:52.008 --> 00:00:53.705
I can't promise you

18
00:00:53.836 --> 00:00:57.144
that New Eden can
support life long-term.

19
00:00:57.318 --> 00:00:59.599
The track is so bad. it's
impossible to find a good speed.

20
00:00:59.624 --> 00:01:00.285
♪

21
00:01:02.000 --> 00:01:08.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

22
00:01:09.634 --> 00:01:10.634
Welcome to the new world.

23
00:01:10.766 --> 00:01:11.854
♪

24
00:01:12.028 --> 00:01:13.203
[Explosion]

25
00:01:13.421 --> 00:01:14.082
♪

26
00:02:11.522 --> 00:02:15.787
In middle school. I spent
an entire summer inside.

27
00:02:15.874 --> 00:02:17.746
I didn't go out.

28
00:02:17.833 --> 00:02:20.662
Didn't want the kids to
make fun of my braces.

29
00:02:20.792 --> 00:02:22.751
But this...

30
00:02:22.838 --> 00:02:26.929
no walls. no ceiling

31
00:02:27.016 --> 00:02:30.019
for the first time
in eight years.

32
00:02:30.106 --> 00:02:33.631
I'm not going to lie. it's
kind of freaking me out.

33
00:02:37.679 --> 00:02:39.594
Does it freak you out?

34
00:02:39.681 --> 00:02:41.639
Not one bit.

35
00:02:41.726 --> 00:02:42.858
But you in braces?

36
00:02:42.945 --> 00:02:44.903
[whistles and chuckles]

37
00:02:44.990 --> 00:02:46.731
<i>All right.</i>

38
00:02:46.818 --> 00:02:49.125
<i>Radiation levels
are normal for now.</i>

39
00:02:49.212 --> 00:02:53.390
Outside temperature
is minus 117.

40
00:02:53.477 --> 00:02:55.087
Maybe it was a...

41
00:02:55.175 --> 00:02:57.438
a satellite that
fell out of orbit.

42
00:03:01.964 --> 00:03:04.793
The rocket's trajectory
was leaving the atmosphere.

43
00:03:04.923 --> 00:03:06.838
not entering it.

44
00:03:06.925 --> 00:03:09.145
<i>Could have been a fail safe
triggered automatically</i>

45
00:03:09.232 --> 00:03:11.887
<i>by who knows what.</i>

46
00:03:11.974 --> 00:03:14.324
A rat chewing a wire?

47
00:03:14.455 --> 00:03:16.631
<i>Yeah. well. anything's possible.</i>

48
00:03:16.718 --> 00:03:18.415
Tell you what.

49
00:03:18.502 --> 00:03:21.288
Let's get these
samples and be gone.

50
00:03:25.161 --> 00:03:27.729
"Snowpiercer." this is Ben.

51
00:03:27.816 --> 00:03:29.339
Do you read me?

52
00:03:29.426 --> 00:03:31.036
<i>[static]</i>

53
00:03:31.123 --> 00:03:32.777
Mel. do you copy? Come in.

54
00:03:32.864 --> 00:03:34.692
<i>[static]</i>

55
00:03:34.779 --> 00:03:36.477
Some kind of interference.

56
00:03:41.699 --> 00:03:44.702
<i>[tense music]</i>

57
00:03:44.789 --> 00:03:45.921
<i>♪ ♪</i>

58
00:03:46.008 --> 00:03:47.792
Ben.

59
00:03:47.879 --> 00:03:48.540
<i>♪ ♪</i>

60
00:03:59.978 --> 00:04:02.242
Holy shit.

61
00:04:02.329 --> 00:04:05.462
<i>[animals screeching. growling]</i>

62
00:04:05.549 --> 00:04:08.944
<i>♪ ♪</i>

63
00:04:09.031 --> 00:04:11.686
They were waiting for us.

64
00:04:18.345 --> 00:04:22.131
<i>The end of the line.</i>

65
00:04:22.218 --> 00:04:24.394
<i>That's what I thought when
the train split apart.</i>

66
00:04:24.525 --> 00:04:27.136
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

67
00:04:27.267 --> 00:04:29.660
<i>Who knew we'd end up like this?</i>

68
00:04:29.747 --> 00:04:34.535
<i>♪ ♪</i>

69
00:04:34.622 --> 00:04:36.972
- Hey. hey. hey. hey. hey. hey.
- I... I got it.

70
00:04:37.102 --> 00:04:38.582
I got... I got it.

71
00:04:38.669 --> 00:04:40.232
You didn't need to run
off like a crazy person.

72
00:04:40.236 --> 00:04:41.411
She's fine.

73
00:04:41.542 --> 00:04:43.326
Come here a second.

74
00:04:43.457 --> 00:04:44.845
You all right? Do
you need to sit down?

75
00:04:44.849 --> 00:04:46.416
You look like you're
going to pass out.

76
00:04:46.547 --> 00:04:47.631
I'm just... well. look.
wait till nap time

77
00:04:47.635 --> 00:04:48.632
when she's screaming
for her Gibby.

78
00:04:48.636 --> 00:04:49.985
Then we gonna see
who the hero is.

79
00:04:50.072 --> 00:04:50.808
- Ain't that right?
- Clearly it's Gibby.

80
00:04:50.812 --> 00:04:52.901
Mm-hmm.

81
00:04:52.988 --> 00:04:54.290
All right. well. now that
you got your morning run in.

82
00:04:54.294 --> 00:04:56.905
how about we all get to work?

83
00:04:57.035 --> 00:04:59.168
Wait. wait. It's cold out.

84
00:04:59.299 --> 00:05:00.691
She needs a...
she needs a parka.

85
00:05:00.778 --> 00:05:02.472
- Mm-hmm. Let me get mine.
- I'll get yours.

86
00:05:02.476 --> 00:05:05.740
<i>Turns out my mother was right.</i>

87
00:05:05.827 --> 00:05:08.133
<i>Before she passed on. she
held my hand and said.</i>

88
00:05:08.220 --> 00:05:10.310
<i>"Don't worry. son.</i>

89
00:05:10.397 --> 00:05:14.662
<i>Endings are just
beginnings in disguise."</i>

90
00:05:14.749 --> 00:05:17.055
<i>[soft upbeat music]</i>

91
00:05:17.142 --> 00:05:21.625
<i>♪ ♪</i>

92
00:05:21.712 --> 00:05:26.891
<i>This is a new
beginning. a new Eden.</i>

93
00:05:26.978 --> 00:05:31.069
<i>filled with survivors
looking for a second chance.</i>

94
00:05:31.156 --> 00:05:34.812
<i>No doubt the open
sky has been a gift.</i>

95
00:05:34.943 --> 00:05:38.338
<i>But growing food.
generating power.</i>

96
00:05:38.425 --> 00:05:41.079
<i>fighting unpredictable weather.</i>

97
00:05:41.166 --> 00:05:43.952
<i>it's been a struggle.</i>

98
00:05:44.039 --> 00:05:48.130
<i>Almost as hard as trying to
make contact with our friends.</i>

99
00:05:48.217 --> 00:05:51.002
<i>Wondering if they're
still alive out there.</i>

100
00:05:51.133 --> 00:05:53.527
<i>on Snowpiercer.</i>

101
00:05:53.614 --> 00:05:56.312
<i>879 cars long.</i>

102
00:05:56.399 --> 00:05:59.271
<i>[dramatic upbeat music]</i>

103
00:05:59.359 --> 00:06:00.020
<i>♪ ♪</i>

104
00:06:05.756 --> 00:06:08.716
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

105
00:06:08.803 --> 00:06:09.464
<i>♪ ♪</i>

106
00:06:24.949 --> 00:06:26.908
<i>Hurry!</i>

107
00:06:26.995 --> 00:06:29.127
<i>Come on. let's go!</i>

108
00:06:29.214 --> 00:06:30.868
<i>[soft upbeat music]</i>

109
00:06:30.955 --> 00:06:32.870
<i>Come on!</i>

110
00:06:33.001 --> 00:06:34.524
<i>Come on. guys!</i>

111
00:06:34.611 --> 00:06:35.830
<i>♪ ♪</i>

112
00:06:35.917 --> 00:06:37.440
There!

113
00:06:37.527 --> 00:06:38.746
Whoa. whoa. whoa.

114
00:06:38.833 --> 00:06:40.182
[chuckles]

115
00:06:40.269 --> 00:06:43.011
Good morning. [Chuckles]

116
00:06:43.098 --> 00:06:44.665
There's a council
meeting tonight?

117
00:06:44.752 --> 00:06:47.058
Yeah. Do you think
you can take her?

118
00:06:47.189 --> 00:06:49.104
Yeah. Just come on
by in the morning.

119
00:06:49.191 --> 00:06:50.975
<i>I'll remember to pack the bunny.</i>

120
00:06:51.062 --> 00:06:52.237
Hey. yeah. what's up?

121
00:06:52.324 --> 00:06:53.848
<i>[chuckles]</i>

122
00:06:53.978 --> 00:06:55.149
Hey. do you think
Headwood has the time

123
00:06:55.153 --> 00:06:56.372
for treatment today?

124
00:06:56.459 --> 00:06:58.243
Yeah. we'll make time for you.

125
00:06:58.330 --> 00:06:59.854
Are you getting
your feeling back?

126
00:06:59.941 --> 00:07:01.769
Yeah.

127
00:07:01.899 --> 00:07:03.979
I mean. some areas are
responding better than others.

128
00:07:04.032 --> 00:07:06.295
I mean. my hand is almost
completely back to normal.

129
00:07:06.426 --> 00:07:08.210
Hey. look! Got lucky.

130
00:07:08.297 --> 00:07:09.559
Actual blueberries.

131
00:07:09.646 --> 00:07:12.519
<i>- OK.</i>
- Ooh. yum.

132
00:07:12.606 --> 00:07:14.303
- Yum.
- Hey.

133
00:07:14.390 --> 00:07:16.127
So I've been working on
that transceiver glitch.

134
00:07:16.131 --> 00:07:17.345
I think the far relay's
too close to the edge

135
00:07:17.349 --> 00:07:18.786
of the pocket.

136
00:07:18.916 --> 00:07:20.356
Yeah. good morning
to you. too. Javi.

137
00:07:20.396 --> 00:07:21.741
Hey. guys. I should
get to the clinic.

138
00:07:21.745 --> 00:07:23.355
- I'll just catch you guys later.
<i>- Yeah.</i>

139
00:07:23.443 --> 00:07:25.053
- Thank you.
- Mm-hmm.

140
00:07:25.140 --> 00:07:27.621
Based on projections.
we've got about a week

141
00:07:27.708 --> 00:07:29.971
before Snowpiercer
reaches radio range.

142
00:07:30.058 --> 00:07:32.277
<i>Yeah. and these atmospheric
conditions are not helping.</i>

143
00:07:32.364 --> 00:07:33.670
<i>They're all over the place.</i>

144
00:07:33.757 --> 00:07:35.716
I think they're
affecting signal.

145
00:07:35.803 --> 00:07:38.414
<i>[tense music]</i>

146
00:07:38.501 --> 00:07:40.068
<i>But I was thinking maybe we can</i>

147
00:07:40.155 --> 00:07:42.331
run diagnostics.
check the feed line.

148
00:07:42.462 --> 00:07:44.333
maybe move one of the relays.

149
00:07:44.420 --> 00:07:45.987
Yes. OK. I'll help.

150
00:07:46.117 --> 00:07:47.118
Thank you.

151
00:07:47.205 --> 00:07:49.207
See you tonight.

152
00:07:49.338 --> 00:07:52.210
[indistinct chatter]

153
00:08:00.131 --> 00:08:01.698
I mean. the fact that we still

154
00:08:01.785 --> 00:08:02.652
have everyone living on
the train after a year.

155
00:08:02.656 --> 00:08:04.353
I'd hoped for much better.

156
00:08:04.484 --> 00:08:06.438
Shelter's next on the list
after we fix the bridge.

157
00:08:06.442 --> 00:08:08.139
Took up a lot of manpower.

158
00:08:08.226 --> 00:08:09.615
Is that still on schedule
to finish this week?

159
00:08:09.619 --> 00:08:11.360
It's...

160
00:08:11.491 --> 00:08:13.449
- we'll get there.
- We better.

161
00:08:13.536 --> 00:08:15.843
You know. the work is piling
up between the shelters.

162
00:08:15.930 --> 00:08:18.323
- the power grid...
- I know. and the relay issues.

163
00:08:18.410 --> 00:08:20.064
The fun never stops.

164
00:08:20.151 --> 00:08:20.974
Are we having relay issues?

165
00:08:20.978 --> 00:08:22.153
Hmm?

166
00:08:22.240 --> 00:08:24.765
Where'd you hear that?

167
00:08:24.852 --> 00:08:26.680
Oh. God. Take me
back to the Teals.

168
00:08:26.767 --> 00:08:29.421
Hey. I think that
rugged town mayor

169
00:08:29.509 --> 00:08:33.164
suits you better than the Teals.

170
00:08:33.251 --> 00:08:36.080
Sorry to bother you. Ruth.
but Sykes needs you in Ag-Sec.

171
00:08:36.211 --> 00:08:38.343
Something about the
irrigation in car A14.

172
00:08:38.430 --> 00:08:40.258
Ooh. there it is.

173
00:08:40.345 --> 00:08:41.691
Let's add irrigation to the
ever-growing list of problems

174
00:08:41.695 --> 00:08:43.610
- for tonight's meeting.
- On it.

175
00:08:43.697 --> 00:08:45.742
That is. if you'll be joining
us. Councilman Layton?

176
00:08:45.873 --> 00:08:47.305
Wouldn't miss it.
Council Chair Wardell.

177
00:08:47.309 --> 00:08:49.964
<i>[soft suspenseful music]</i>

178
00:08:50.051 --> 00:08:50.712
<i>♪ ♪</i>

179
00:09:09.549 --> 00:09:11.459
Man. I don't know what
everybody's complaining about.

180
00:09:11.463 --> 00:09:13.727
We got open sky. fresh air.

181
00:09:13.814 --> 00:09:16.207
Yeah. they complaining
a lot or a little?

182
00:09:16.294 --> 00:09:17.948
Uh. medium.

183
00:09:18.035 --> 00:09:18.858
Either way. beats
the days of the Tail.

184
00:09:18.862 --> 00:09:19.950
Know what I'm sayin'?

185
00:09:20.037 --> 00:09:20.995
<i>Hey.</i>

186
00:09:21.082 --> 00:09:22.605
[grunts]

187
00:09:22.692 --> 00:09:23.911
- Shit. Hey.
<i>- Hey. hey. hey!</i>

188
00:09:24.041 --> 00:09:25.173
Hey!

189
00:09:25.260 --> 00:09:26.740
Cut it out!

190
00:09:26.827 --> 00:09:29.046
Hey. break it up!
Boki. Drop him!

191
00:09:29.133 --> 00:09:30.744
- No!
- Put him down!

192
00:09:30.831 --> 00:09:32.528
Shit.

193
00:09:32.615 --> 00:09:34.486
All right. hey.
hey. Stop. stop!

194
00:09:34.574 --> 00:09:35.483
What is wrong with y'all?

195
00:09:35.487 --> 00:09:36.576
He doesn't pay attention.

196
00:09:36.663 --> 00:09:38.403
He almost killed me with beam!

197
00:09:38.534 --> 00:09:39.749
Well. you weren't looking.
you bloody Frankenstein.

198
00:09:39.753 --> 00:09:41.537
- Back up.
- He's drunk. He's drunk.

199
00:09:41.624 --> 00:09:42.146
- I'm not drunk.
- He's always drunk!

200
00:09:42.233 --> 00:09:43.757
Hey! All right!

201
00:09:43.844 --> 00:09:45.015
We don't have time
for this shit!

202
00:09:45.019 --> 00:09:46.716
We are so close to
finishing this bridge!

203
00:09:48.979 --> 00:09:51.068
Look at you. man.
You're a mess.

204
00:09:51.155 --> 00:09:53.201
Go get yourself stitched up.

205
00:09:53.288 --> 00:09:56.421
This is not the paradise
we were promised.

206
00:10:04.647 --> 00:10:07.389
Try not to use this
hand for a few days.

207
00:10:07.476 --> 00:10:09.316
If you make a fist. it'll
rip the stitches. OK?

208
00:10:09.391 --> 00:10:10.522
Mm-hmm.

209
00:10:10.610 --> 00:10:11.480
[cooing]

210
00:10:11.611 --> 00:10:13.830
[chuckles]

211
00:10:13.917 --> 00:10:15.702
Yeah. [baby giggling]

212
00:10:15.789 --> 00:10:17.791
Wanna tell me what happened?

213
00:10:17.878 --> 00:10:19.270
Not really. no.

214
00:10:22.273 --> 00:10:23.623
I hear the bridge
is almost done.

215
00:10:23.710 --> 00:10:25.581
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

216
00:10:25.668 --> 00:10:26.752
I don't understand
why we're trying

217
00:10:26.756 --> 00:10:28.715
to reunite with those people.

218
00:10:28.802 --> 00:10:30.002
<i>What do you mean. Snowpiercer?</i>

219
00:10:30.064 --> 00:10:32.109
Yeah.

220
00:10:32.196 --> 00:10:35.199
<i>Well. some of our friends
are still on that train.</i>

221
00:10:35.286 --> 00:10:37.506
Yeah. not mine.

222
00:10:37.593 --> 00:10:39.073
Well. if you have any issues.

223
00:10:39.160 --> 00:10:42.685
you can always bring them up
at the Council. Town Hall.

224
00:10:42.772 --> 00:10:45.166
Hey. they have music
there sometimes.

225
00:10:45.253 --> 00:10:46.863
You used to play
the piano. right?

226
00:10:46.950 --> 00:10:48.735
<i>♪ ♪</i>

227
00:10:48.822 --> 00:10:52.173
Yeah. something.
in the Nightcar.

228
00:10:52.260 --> 00:10:54.392
Maybe if it comes back.
you can play again.

229
00:10:54.479 --> 00:10:57.178
<i>[soft tense music]</i>

230
00:10:57.265 --> 00:11:00.007
<i>♪ ♪</i>

231
00:11:00.137 --> 00:11:01.835
Thank you for this.

232
00:11:01.922 --> 00:11:05.534
<i>♪ ♪</i>

233
00:11:05.621 --> 00:11:08.624
[indistinct chatter]

234
00:11:08.711 --> 00:11:09.372
<i>♪ ♪</i>

235
00:11:28.296 --> 00:11:30.298
Am I late?

236
00:11:30.385 --> 00:11:31.865
<i>♪ ♪</i>

237
00:11:31.952 --> 00:11:33.472
Welcome. everyone.
to tonight's meeting

238
00:11:33.518 --> 00:11:35.520
of the council of New Eden.

239
00:11:35.607 --> 00:11:37.958
Let the minutes show that all
members are present save one.

240
00:11:38.045 --> 00:11:40.090
Yeah. what's Alex up to tonight?

241
00:11:40.177 --> 00:11:42.136
She was up in the
hill earlier today.

242
00:11:42.223 --> 00:11:43.303
I don't know if she's back.

243
00:11:43.354 --> 00:11:44.486
Checking the readings?

244
00:11:44.573 --> 00:11:45.313
She didn't say.

245
00:11:45.443 --> 00:11:47.184
All right.

246
00:11:47.315 --> 00:11:49.709
I move that we declare
Alex's chair vacant again.

247
00:11:49.796 --> 00:11:51.362
- Agreed?
- Hey. it's her loss.

248
00:11:51.449 --> 00:11:53.016
Agreed.

249
00:11:53.103 --> 00:11:54.753
Right. the main issue
on the docket tonight

250
00:11:54.757 --> 00:11:56.672
is the strain on our
already limited resources

251
00:11:56.759 --> 00:11:58.456
should Snowpiercer return.

252
00:11:58.543 --> 00:12:00.458
I just... I was thinking
that while we have

253
00:12:00.545 --> 00:12:03.157
this very serious
discussion about survival...

254
00:12:03.244 --> 00:12:04.197
<i>- Ah.
- We live a little.</i>

255
00:12:04.201 --> 00:12:05.855
Yes!

256
00:12:05.942 --> 00:12:07.182
<i>Ah. come on. it's been a while.</i>

257
00:12:07.204 --> 00:12:09.076
I defer to the council chair.

258
00:12:09.163 --> 00:12:10.294
<i>[soft upbeat music]</i>

259
00:12:10.381 --> 00:12:11.861
Oh. fine. Chair agrees.

260
00:12:11.948 --> 00:12:13.863
[cheers and laughter]

261
00:12:13.950 --> 00:12:14.908
Let's do it.

262
00:12:14.995 --> 00:12:16.997
- Ruth. say when.
- When.

263
00:12:17.084 --> 00:12:18.298
- Say when.
- When. You don't listen!

264
00:12:18.302 --> 00:12:19.477
All right.

265
00:12:19.564 --> 00:12:20.609
Yay. your move.

266
00:12:20.696 --> 00:12:22.916
It's hold 'em.

267
00:12:23.003 --> 00:12:24.914
And just for this one hand.
if you will indulge me.

268
00:12:24.918 --> 00:12:26.397
kings are wild.

269
00:12:26.528 --> 00:12:27.830
- All right.
- Just the way they like it.

270
00:12:27.834 --> 00:12:29.574
[laughter]

271
00:12:29.661 --> 00:12:31.268
Shh. Jos. keep our business
out the street. babe.

272
00:12:31.272 --> 00:12:32.403
[laughter]

273
00:12:32.490 --> 00:12:35.406
[wind howling]

274
00:12:35.493 --> 00:12:38.888
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

275
00:12:38.975 --> 00:12:39.636
<i>♪ ♪</i>

276
00:12:54.295 --> 00:12:57.254
[pigeon cooing]

277
00:12:57.341 --> 00:13:00.170
<i>♪ ♪</i>

278
00:13:00.257 --> 00:13:03.086
Hey. Mr. Sprinkles.
You miss me?

279
00:13:03.173 --> 00:13:04.174
[coos]

280
00:13:04.261 --> 00:13:04.922
<i>♪ ♪</i>

281
00:13:19.407 --> 00:13:21.104
[sniffles]

282
00:13:21.191 --> 00:13:23.454
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

283
00:13:23.541 --> 00:13:24.202
<i>♪ ♪</i>

284
00:13:29.504 --> 00:13:31.114
[sniffles]

285
00:13:31.201 --> 00:13:32.550
<i>What I'm saying
is that rigging up</i>

286
00:13:32.637 --> 00:13:33.330
<i>a geothermal heat
exchanger for a whole town</i>

287
00:13:33.334 --> 00:13:35.466
is not that simple.

288
00:13:35.553 --> 00:13:37.421
But Snowpiercer's return will
only make it more complicated.

289
00:13:37.425 --> 00:13:39.345
It's more shelters to
build. more mouths to feed.

290
00:13:39.383 --> 00:13:41.124
more energy to generate.

291
00:13:41.211 --> 00:13:42.774
Yeah. but if we can get
geothermal and solar

292
00:13:42.778 --> 00:13:45.085
running 20% of
the grid by winter

293
00:13:45.172 --> 00:13:47.522
and then Big Alice
running the rest.

294
00:13:47.609 --> 00:13:51.439
it'll be cold. but we won't
freeze to death. I think.

295
00:13:51.526 --> 00:13:53.136
I see your 5 and raise you 10.

296
00:13:53.267 --> 00:13:54.834
<i>- Huh. huh.</i>
- Ooh.

297
00:13:54.921 --> 00:13:56.531
He's holding aces.

298
00:13:56.618 --> 00:13:58.398
Snowpiercer comes with
its own resources. too.

299
00:13:58.402 --> 00:14:01.971
It's got more Ag-Sec. more
equipment. larger workforce.

300
00:14:02.058 --> 00:14:04.365
Yes. but the pocket that we
inhabit is only so large.

301
00:14:04.452 --> 00:14:05.710
Maybe there isn't
room for both trains.

302
00:14:05.714 --> 00:14:08.717
[indistinct chatter]

303
00:14:08.804 --> 00:14:12.503
<i>♪ ♪</i>

304
00:14:12.590 --> 00:14:13.940
I don't know if
you guys noticed.

305
00:14:14.027 --> 00:14:15.550
but Javi isn't even
paying attention.

306
00:14:15.637 --> 00:14:16.764
- He's killing us.
- I noticed.

307
00:14:16.768 --> 00:14:18.814
He always does.

308
00:14:18.901 --> 00:14:19.336
- Fold.
<i>- Solid choice.</i>

309
00:14:19.423 --> 00:14:21.512
[laughter]

310
00:14:21.599 --> 00:14:24.124
All right. Mr. Roche.

311
00:14:24.211 --> 00:14:26.517
I call.

312
00:14:26.604 --> 00:14:27.692
<i>Let's see it.</i>

313
00:14:27.779 --> 00:14:29.216
Check that out right there.

314
00:14:29.303 --> 00:14:30.695
<i>- No!</i>
- Pair of 3s.

315
00:14:30.782 --> 00:14:32.262
- [laughter]
<i>- No!</i>

316
00:14:32.349 --> 00:14:34.743
<i>- No!</i>
- 3s? 3s!

317
00:14:34.830 --> 00:14:35.831
He came at him with 3s!

318
00:14:35.918 --> 00:14:37.920
[indistinct chatter]

319
00:14:38.007 --> 00:14:40.923
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

320
00:14:41.010 --> 00:14:42.185
<i>♪ ♪</i>

321
00:14:42.272 --> 00:14:43.665
- [laughter]
- How!

322
00:14:43.752 --> 00:14:44.971
How do you do it. Mr. Vegas?

323
00:14:45.058 --> 00:14:46.494
- It's all magic.
- Nope.

324
00:14:46.581 --> 00:14:48.017
You want the truth?

325
00:14:48.104 --> 00:14:50.715
No. lie to me. Yes. the truth.

326
00:14:50.846 --> 00:14:52.630
<i>So when I was a kid.</i>

327
00:14:52.717 --> 00:14:54.937
<i>I worked with my cousins at
a restaurant in Monteria.</i>

328
00:14:55.024 --> 00:14:56.678
But after work. we'd
go to the back room.

329
00:14:56.765 --> 00:14:58.549
play cards all night.

330
00:14:58.636 --> 00:15:00.243
By the time I was 16. I
was able to read everyone.

331
00:15:00.247 --> 00:15:03.206
<i>I read their</i> pistas...

332
00:15:03.293 --> 00:15:04.860
clues. Read their clues.

333
00:15:04.947 --> 00:15:05.944
Oh. you mean their tells?

334
00:15:05.948 --> 00:15:06.858
Yes. I read your tells.

335
00:15:06.862 --> 00:15:09.604
OK. what's my <i>pista?</i>

336
00:15:09.691 --> 00:15:12.999
[chuckles] Your
<i>pistas.</i> Layton.

337
00:15:13.086 --> 00:15:14.914
on a good hand. you
lean back on your chair.

338
00:15:15.001 --> 00:15:16.480
all slow-like.

339
00:15:16.567 --> 00:15:20.049
<i>You're super
dramatic.</i> [laughter]

340
00:15:20.136 --> 00:15:21.746
What about Mr. Roche here?

341
00:15:21.833 --> 00:15:23.923
Mr. Roche. you check
your whole cards twice

342
00:15:24.010 --> 00:15:25.707
- just to make sure.
- What?

343
00:15:25.794 --> 00:15:28.275
Yeah. And you. Josie.
you play with your hair.

344
00:15:28.362 --> 00:15:30.190
<i>Exactly. Like that.</i> [laughter]

345
00:15:30.277 --> 00:15:32.192
<i>Ruth... Ruth.
you're the easiest.</i>

346
00:15:32.279 --> 00:15:34.890
On a bad hand. your
left eyebrow will go up.

347
00:15:34.977 --> 00:15:37.240
You'll raise it.
Just your left.

348
00:15:37.327 --> 00:15:38.977
- I'm gonna start watching now.
- I told you this.

349
00:15:38.981 --> 00:15:40.722
I can't play with
you guys anymore.

350
00:15:40.809 --> 00:15:42.854
Whoa. what happened?

351
00:15:42.942 --> 00:15:44.595
[indistinct exclamations]

352
00:15:44.682 --> 00:15:46.423
Well. if Ag-Sec lose power...

353
00:15:46.510 --> 00:15:48.208
Yeah. I'm on it.

354
00:15:48.295 --> 00:15:50.210
[indistinct exclamations]

355
00:15:50.340 --> 00:15:51.951
<i>I'll count your chips for you.</i>

356
00:15:52.038 --> 00:15:53.169
[Javi chuckles]

357
00:15:56.694 --> 00:15:59.610
[Javi humming]

358
00:15:59.697 --> 00:16:02.222
[wind howling]

359
00:16:13.581 --> 00:16:15.322
[sloshing]

360
00:16:25.897 --> 00:16:28.552
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

361
00:16:28.639 --> 00:16:31.207
<i>♪ ♪</i>

362
00:16:31.294 --> 00:16:33.601
<i>Qué carajo?</i>

363
00:16:33.688 --> 00:16:34.349
<i>♪ ♪</i>

364
00:16:40.042 --> 00:16:41.609
[electricity humming]

365
00:16:41.696 --> 00:16:43.828
[rocks tumbling]

366
00:16:43.915 --> 00:16:48.616
<i>♪ ♪</i>

367
00:16:48.703 --> 00:16:51.662
[rocks tumbling] [Javi gasps]

368
00:16:51.749 --> 00:16:52.410
<i>♪ ♪</i>

369
00:16:58.017 --> 00:16:59.666
If this is some kind of
joke. it's not funny.

370
00:16:59.670 --> 00:17:03.761
<i>♪ ♪</i>

371
00:17:03.848 --> 00:17:06.808
[wind howling]

372
00:17:06.895 --> 00:17:07.556
<i>♪ ♪</i>

373
00:17:29.178 --> 00:17:30.962
[smooches]

374
00:17:31.050 --> 00:17:32.877
- Feel that?
- Mm-hmm.

375
00:17:32.964 --> 00:17:34.444
- Mm-hmm?
- Maybe.

376
00:17:34.575 --> 00:17:35.532
Mm.

377
00:17:35.619 --> 00:17:36.446
[Josie chuckles]

378
00:17:36.533 --> 00:17:37.447
All right.

379
00:17:37.534 --> 00:17:38.535
[smooches]

380
00:17:38.622 --> 00:17:39.754
[chuckles] Mm.

381
00:17:39.841 --> 00:17:40.668
Mm.

382
00:17:40.755 --> 00:17:42.365
[smooches]

383
00:17:42.452 --> 00:17:44.846
Yeah. well. I think
Dr. Headwood's treatment

384
00:17:44.933 --> 00:17:46.413
is working quite well.

385
00:17:46.500 --> 00:17:48.197
Yeah? [chuckles]

386
00:17:48.284 --> 00:17:50.808
<i>[soft upbeat music playing]</i>

387
00:17:50.895 --> 00:17:53.115
[moans]

388
00:17:53.202 --> 00:17:55.117
<i>♪ ♪</i>

389
00:17:55.204 --> 00:17:56.814
[chuckles] Now can
we kill the lights?

390
00:17:56.901 --> 00:17:59.469
Mm-hmm.

391
00:17:59.556 --> 00:18:00.217
<i>♪ ♪</i>

392
00:18:05.127 --> 00:18:06.650
Javi thinks it was an accident.

393
00:18:06.737 --> 00:18:08.561
but who goes fumbling
around the back of town hall

394
00:18:08.565 --> 00:18:11.177
and trips over a power cord?

395
00:18:11.264 --> 00:18:12.874
You want to talk about this now?

396
00:18:12.961 --> 00:18:14.480
Not everyone loves the idea
of Snowpiercer coming back.

397
00:18:14.484 --> 00:18:16.095
Ugh.

398
00:18:16.182 --> 00:18:17.483
What if somebody is trying
to send us a message?

399
00:18:17.487 --> 00:18:18.789
Then somebody is gonna
have to get over it.

400
00:18:18.793 --> 00:18:20.099
[both chuckle] Come on!

401
00:18:20.186 --> 00:18:21.096
I mean. it's not
about the train.

402
00:18:21.100 --> 00:18:23.276
It's about the people.

403
00:18:23.363 --> 00:18:25.147
Every day I wonder about Miles.

404
00:18:25.234 --> 00:18:26.931
How tall he's got. where he is.

405
00:18:27.018 --> 00:18:28.368
Mm.

406
00:18:28.455 --> 00:18:30.892
Ben. too.

407
00:18:30.979 --> 00:18:32.720
Melanie. not so much.

408
00:18:32.807 --> 00:18:35.114
[Layton chuckles]

409
00:18:35.201 --> 00:18:38.029
Come here.

410
00:18:41.294 --> 00:18:42.726
How long have those
power relays been

411
00:18:42.730 --> 00:18:46.516
giving you and Javi problems?

412
00:18:46.603 --> 00:18:48.166
You can go and talk to
Javi about that right now.

413
00:18:48.170 --> 00:18:51.304
or we can stay
here and get naked.

414
00:18:51.391 --> 00:18:52.475
Yeah. that's my bad.
[Josie chuckles]

415
00:18:52.479 --> 00:18:53.737
I don't know what
I was thinking.

416
00:18:53.741 --> 00:18:55.786
[both chuckle]

417
00:18:55.873 --> 00:18:58.833
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

418
00:18:58.920 --> 00:19:01.575
<i>♪ ♪</i>

419
00:19:01.662 --> 00:19:04.839
[wind howling]

420
00:19:04.926 --> 00:19:06.841
<i>♪ ♪</i>

421
00:19:08.930 --> 00:19:11.411
<i>[garbled radio message]</i>

422
00:19:11.541 --> 00:19:14.936
<i>[static buzzing]</i>

423
00:19:15.023 --> 00:19:17.460
<i>Can anybody hear me?</i>

424
00:19:17.547 --> 00:19:19.288
New Eden to Snowpiercer.
Do you copy?

425
00:19:19.375 --> 00:19:21.508
<i>Is any... there?</i>

426
00:19:21.595 --> 00:19:22.987
<i>♪ ♪</i>

427
00:19:23.074 --> 00:19:27.514
Snowpiercer. do you copy?

428
00:19:27.601 --> 00:19:29.646
Come on. come on.

429
00:19:29.733 --> 00:19:30.394
<i>♪ ♪</i>

430
00:19:35.870 --> 00:19:38.525
Mel. this is Javi.

431
00:19:38.612 --> 00:19:40.657
<i>♪ ♪</i>

432
00:19:40.788 --> 00:19:42.485
Ben. do you copy?

433
00:19:42.572 --> 00:19:43.233
<i>♪ ♪</i>

434
00:19:55.498 --> 00:19:58.414
[indistinct chatter]

435
00:19:58.501 --> 00:20:02.897
<i>♪ ♪</i>

436
00:20:02.984 --> 00:20:04.507
Can you take a step?

437
00:20:04.638 --> 00:20:05.678
You take a step for Daddy?

438
00:20:09.077 --> 00:20:11.340
<i>One step for Daddy. No?</i>

439
00:20:11.427 --> 00:20:12.863
Will you do it for Gibby?

440
00:20:12.950 --> 00:20:14.474
One step for Gibby?

441
00:20:14.561 --> 00:20:16.389
[chuckles] Don't
worry. It'll happen.

442
00:20:16.476 --> 00:20:18.042
<i>- Ah.
- Ah.</i>

443
00:20:18.129 --> 00:20:19.870
Hey. mama's.

444
00:20:20.001 --> 00:20:22.743
Oh. I don't know why
I'm trying so hard.

445
00:20:22.830 --> 00:20:24.745
One day. she's taking
her first steps.

446
00:20:24.832 --> 00:20:26.395
The next day. she's
walking right out that door

447
00:20:26.399 --> 00:20:28.052
in that cold. scary world.

448
00:20:28.139 --> 00:20:29.750
<i>Will you stop it?</i>

449
00:20:29.837 --> 00:20:32.274
Whatever comes.
Liana will be ready.

450
00:20:32.361 --> 00:20:33.623
She's a fighter.

451
00:20:33.710 --> 00:20:35.756
Mm-hmm. Just like her mother.

452
00:20:36.844 --> 00:20:38.324
Just like her father.

453
00:20:43.851 --> 00:20:47.550
Hey. I patched Oz up after
that tussle he had with Boki.

454
00:20:47.637 --> 00:20:49.248
I heard you were the
one who broke it up.

455
00:20:49.335 --> 00:20:52.642
Yeah. Oz has got issues.

456
00:20:52.773 --> 00:20:54.601
<i>Ha!</i>

457
00:20:54.688 --> 00:20:56.599
What made him leave town
and move up on the mountain?

458
00:20:56.603 --> 00:20:58.735
<i>He didn't tell me.</i>

459
00:20:58.822 --> 00:21:01.738
But every day he's up
there. the weirder he gets.

460
00:21:01.825 --> 00:21:03.000
- [cooing]
- Yeah?

461
00:21:03.087 --> 00:21:04.001
<i>I think you're right.</i>

462
00:21:04.088 --> 00:21:05.394
We're gonna try it again!

463
00:21:05.481 --> 00:21:06.870
We're gonna try it
again. All right.

464
00:21:06.874 --> 00:21:08.310
- Baby.
- Give me your hand.

465
00:21:08.397 --> 00:21:09.442
Come on.

466
00:21:09.529 --> 00:21:11.270
Can you... oh. oh. oh!

467
00:21:11.357 --> 00:21:12.793
That was a step!

468
00:21:12.880 --> 00:21:14.882
That was a step. you genius!

469
00:21:14.969 --> 00:21:16.532
<i>- You did it. baby!</i>
- She walked with me.

470
00:21:16.536 --> 00:21:17.580
You saw it.

471
00:21:17.667 --> 00:21:19.408
I saw it. I admit it.

472
00:21:19.495 --> 00:21:21.014
That was for... that
was definitely a...

473
00:21:21.018 --> 00:21:24.021
<i>[soft suspenseful music]</i>

474
00:21:24.108 --> 00:21:25.849
<i>♪ ♪</i>

475
00:21:25.936 --> 00:21:28.852
[wind howling]

476
00:21:28.939 --> 00:21:33.770
♪

477
00:21:33.857 --> 00:21:36.904
<i>[person speaking Gaelic]</i>

478
00:21:36.991 --> 00:21:37.652
<i>♪ ♪</i>

479
00:21:46.522 --> 00:21:49.569
<i>- [person speaking Gaelic]</i>
- Who's there?

480
00:21:49.656 --> 00:21:52.876
<i>[person speaking Gaelic]</i>

481
00:21:52.963 --> 00:21:54.574
Show yourself.

482
00:21:54.661 --> 00:21:55.322
<i>♪ ♪</i>

483
00:22:14.594 --> 00:22:17.423
Hey. did you hear
that radio call?

484
00:22:17.510 --> 00:22:19.512
It sounded to me
like it got cut off.

485
00:22:19.642 --> 00:22:21.383
Josie went out to check
the relay already.

486
00:22:21.514 --> 00:22:23.434
Javi. I'm busy right now.
I can't talk. actually.

487
00:22:24.778 --> 00:22:27.911
It's Snowpiercer.

488
00:22:27.998 --> 00:22:29.300
I think they just
tried to make contact

489
00:22:29.304 --> 00:22:30.610
for the first time in a year.

490
00:22:33.264 --> 00:22:35.310
All right. look. Alex.

491
00:22:35.397 --> 00:22:38.008
I know you've got your
own thing going on.

492
00:22:38.139 --> 00:22:40.184
But you're on the council.

493
00:22:40.271 --> 00:22:42.578
And we have a lot
of responsibility.

494
00:22:42.665 --> 00:22:44.265
Power. comms. water.
Ag-Sec. you name it.

495
00:22:44.275 --> 00:22:47.322
Yep. I was running Big
Alice when I was nine. so.

496
00:22:47.409 --> 00:22:48.802
And you're a genius.

497
00:22:48.889 --> 00:22:51.544
I know that. We all know that.

498
00:22:51.631 --> 00:22:53.546
The fact that you figured out

499
00:22:53.633 --> 00:22:55.457
how Big Alice could generate
power on low idle is like...

500
00:22:55.461 --> 00:22:58.159
Nobel Prize-winning stuff.

501
00:22:58.246 --> 00:23:00.422
I was going to say
impressive. but OK.

502
00:23:02.032 --> 00:23:04.208
Thing is...

503
00:23:04.295 --> 00:23:07.298
Snowpiercer is coming
into comms range.

504
00:23:07.386 --> 00:23:09.997
It could be already.

505
00:23:10.084 --> 00:23:12.652
And that includes your mother.

506
00:23:12.739 --> 00:23:15.263
Out of all people. don't
you want to reach her?

507
00:23:15.350 --> 00:23:17.439
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

508
00:23:17.526 --> 00:23:19.876
Javi. stick to the science.
Stay away from the personal.

509
00:23:19.963 --> 00:23:24.403
Not very good at it. OK?

510
00:23:24.490 --> 00:23:27.971
<i>♪ ♪</i>

511
00:23:28.058 --> 00:23:30.844
<i>[soft tense music]</i>

512
00:23:30.931 --> 00:23:32.846
- [indistinct chatter]
- Layton.

513
00:23:32.933 --> 00:23:34.413
Josie.

514
00:23:40.462 --> 00:23:42.856
Javi thinks he just heard
Snowpiercer on the comms.

515
00:23:42.943 --> 00:23:44.597
but the signal dropped out.

516
00:23:44.684 --> 00:23:46.333
But I mean. if they're
in communications range.

517
00:23:46.337 --> 00:23:48.297
that means they're closing
in on the track switch.

518
00:23:48.383 --> 00:23:49.471
Well ahead of schedule.

519
00:23:49.558 --> 00:23:50.994
But the bridge isn't done yet.

520
00:23:51.081 --> 00:23:52.474
If Snowpiercer's that close...

521
00:23:52.561 --> 00:23:54.389
Look. we need to fix
the relays first.

522
00:23:54.476 --> 00:23:56.082
They can't come here if
they don't know we exist.

523
00:23:56.086 --> 00:23:57.871
Do you think you can
get up there. Josie?

524
00:23:57.958 --> 00:23:59.738
See if that relay's the
reason we lost the signal?

525
00:23:59.742 --> 00:24:03.398
Yeah. I'll go and suit up.

526
00:24:03.529 --> 00:24:04.660
The other relay. though.

527
00:24:04.791 --> 00:24:06.923
it's six. seven
hours' trek away?

528
00:24:07.010 --> 00:24:08.969
Yeah. I'll get Boki.

529
00:24:09.056 --> 00:24:11.058
- Quick as you can.
- I'm on my way.

530
00:24:11.145 --> 00:24:13.234
<i>♪ ♪</i>

531
00:24:13.321 --> 00:24:15.018
Hey. guys.

532
00:24:15.105 --> 00:24:16.367
[tools grinding]

533
00:24:16.455 --> 00:24:18.369
- Hey. Z.
- Yo.

534
00:24:18.457 --> 00:24:20.720
You seen Boki?

535
00:24:20.807 --> 00:24:23.113
He never showed up this morning.

536
00:24:23.200 --> 00:24:24.724
Hey. neither did Oz.

537
00:24:24.811 --> 00:24:25.472
<i>♪ ♪</i>

538
00:24:35.778 --> 00:24:38.912
Whoa. hey. what did we say
about ripping those stitches?

539
00:24:38.999 --> 00:24:41.001
Yeah.

540
00:24:41.088 --> 00:24:44.483
You need to come by the clinic
and get them redone. OK?

541
00:24:44.570 --> 00:24:46.833
Yeah. yeah. yeah.
Yeah. I'll... I'll try.

542
00:24:46.920 --> 00:24:47.581
<i>♪ ♪</i>

543
00:24:59.628 --> 00:25:02.457
[indistinct chatter]

544
00:25:02.544 --> 00:25:05.547
<i>[soft suspenseful music]</i>

545
00:25:05.634 --> 00:25:06.295
<i>♪ ♪</i>

546
00:25:11.335 --> 00:25:12.685
Hey. excuse me.

547
00:25:12.772 --> 00:25:14.817
Can I get your
attention for a minute?

548
00:25:14.904 --> 00:25:17.820
I'm looking for Boki.
Anybody seen him?

549
00:25:17.907 --> 00:25:19.561
<i>- Who?</i>
- Big guy.

550
00:25:19.648 --> 00:25:21.258
Yeah.

551
00:25:21.345 --> 00:25:23.565
I saw him coming out
of the Engine earlier.

552
00:25:23.696 --> 00:25:25.262
- He was up at Big Alice?
- Yeah.

553
00:25:25.349 --> 00:25:26.960
He had a small crate with him.

554
00:25:27.047 --> 00:25:29.179
Looked like he was
heading up into the hills.

555
00:25:29.266 --> 00:25:30.659
All right. OK.

556
00:25:30.746 --> 00:25:32.661
- Thanks. Lights.
<i>- Mm-hmm.</i>

557
00:25:32.748 --> 00:25:35.403
<i>♪ ♪</i>

558
00:25:35.490 --> 00:25:38.362
[wind howling]

559
00:25:38.493 --> 00:25:41.452
<i>[tense music]</i>

560
00:25:41.540 --> 00:25:42.201
<i>♪ ♪</i>

561
00:26:05.259 --> 00:26:06.695
Oh. wow.

562
00:26:06.826 --> 00:26:09.655
Yeah.

563
00:26:09.742 --> 00:26:12.092
Could the rock have fall
off a cliff or something?

564
00:26:12.179 --> 00:26:15.443
Uh. even with the winds the
way they've been. I doubt it.

565
00:26:15.530 --> 00:26:18.185
But this is why we lost
signal this morning.

566
00:26:18.272 --> 00:26:21.014
Power issues. broken relays.

567
00:26:21.101 --> 00:26:22.624
Did you ever find Boki?

568
00:26:22.711 --> 00:26:24.670
He was up at the Engine today.

569
00:26:24.757 --> 00:26:26.397
Javi. Alex say anything
to you about that?

570
00:26:26.410 --> 00:26:28.195
No.

571
00:26:28.282 --> 00:26:30.322
She talks more to Mr. Sprinkles
than she does to me.

572
00:26:30.371 --> 00:26:32.155
I'm sorry. Mr. Sprinkles?

573
00:26:32.242 --> 00:26:33.896
Her pet bird.

574
00:26:33.983 --> 00:26:36.595
She's using him to
get some climate data.

575
00:26:36.682 --> 00:26:38.292
She keep him in a little box?

576
00:26:38.379 --> 00:26:40.120
Yeah. usually. Why?

577
00:26:40.207 --> 00:26:42.644
No. just something Lights said.

578
00:26:42.775 --> 00:26:46.909
Boki's not our guy. Hey.
I think this was sabotage.

579
00:26:46.996 --> 00:26:48.868
<i>Things can't have got that bad.</i>

580
00:26:48.998 --> 00:26:50.474
<i>You said it yourself. The
town's been grumbling.</i>

581
00:26:50.478 --> 00:26:52.915
We can discuss this
tonight at town hall.

582
00:26:53.002 --> 00:26:55.526
and maybe discuss stepping
up security with Mr. Roche.

583
00:26:55.614 --> 00:26:58.312
Javi. can you and Josie either
repair or replace this relay

584
00:26:58.399 --> 00:27:00.270
and get it back on the hillside?

585
00:27:00.357 --> 00:27:01.663
[sighs] It'll be tight.

586
00:27:01.750 --> 00:27:03.056
- But...
- Excellent. Thank you.

587
00:27:03.186 --> 00:27:04.971
Andre. can I have a minute?

588
00:27:09.802 --> 00:27:11.804
<i>In the evening. OK?
Thank you. Sean.</i>

589
00:27:11.934 --> 00:27:15.938
Zarah. sorry. but I have
to step out for a bit.

590
00:27:16.069 --> 00:27:17.548
Sure.

591
00:27:17.636 --> 00:27:19.072
Will you be back this afternoon?

592
00:27:19.159 --> 00:27:20.856
Yes.

593
00:27:20.943 --> 00:27:24.425
I... Boki needs
another skin treatment.

594
00:27:25.600 --> 00:27:27.994
- I'll be back after that.
- OK.

595
00:27:28.124 --> 00:27:30.344
Oz was supposed to stop by
to get his stitches redone.

596
00:27:30.474 --> 00:27:32.041
but he never came.

597
00:27:32.128 --> 00:27:34.435
So I'm going to head
up to see him later.

598
00:27:34.522 --> 00:27:37.786
You're a kind soul.

599
00:27:37.960 --> 00:27:38.621
<i>♪ ♪</i>

600
00:27:55.674 --> 00:27:57.371
This is not the
normal town drama.

601
00:27:57.458 --> 00:27:58.894
There is something
else going on.

602
00:27:58.981 --> 00:28:00.374
And you really
think it's related

603
00:28:00.461 --> 00:28:01.240
to Snowpiercer coming back?

604
00:28:01.244 --> 00:28:03.333
Maybe?

605
00:28:03.420 --> 00:28:05.031
I don't know.

606
00:28:05.118 --> 00:28:06.506
We voted to fix the
bridge a long time ago.

607
00:28:06.510 --> 00:28:08.469
so why fight it now?

608
00:28:10.384 --> 00:28:11.472
Devil's advocate?

609
00:28:16.695 --> 00:28:21.700
Resentment is a powerful thing.

610
00:28:21.787 --> 00:28:24.311
The feeling is that we risked
everything coming here.

611
00:28:24.398 --> 00:28:26.226
Snowpiercer didn't.

612
00:28:26.313 --> 00:28:28.968
They chose to move on.

613
00:28:29.055 --> 00:28:30.447
So why should they
share the reward

614
00:28:30.534 --> 00:28:33.712
when we took all the risk?

615
00:28:33.799 --> 00:28:35.409
Let them live with their choice.

616
00:28:35.496 --> 00:28:38.847
<i>[soft suspenseful music]</i>

617
00:28:38.934 --> 00:28:43.765
Is the devil's advocate
talking. or Ruth Wardell?

618
00:28:43.852 --> 00:28:46.855
We both have friends
on that train.

619
00:28:46.942 --> 00:28:49.597
Friends we'd like to see again.

620
00:28:49.771 --> 00:28:50.641
<i>♪ ♪</i>

621
00:28:50.729 --> 00:28:53.993
Yeah.

622
00:28:54.123 --> 00:28:57.910
Right. well. my opinion.
it's not a protest.

623
00:28:57.997 --> 00:28:59.437
Protesters want to
be seen and heard.

624
00:28:59.520 --> 00:29:00.956
This is different.

625
00:29:01.043 --> 00:29:02.610
This is more like
they're testing us

626
00:29:02.697 --> 00:29:04.394
to see how we're
going to respond.

627
00:29:04.481 --> 00:29:07.093
So the question is. what next?

628
00:29:08.703 --> 00:29:10.836
[sighs] Times like these.

629
00:29:10.923 --> 00:29:12.751
I bet you really
regret stepping down.

630
00:29:12.838 --> 00:29:14.840
[chuckles] Not
even a little bit.

631
00:29:14.927 --> 00:29:16.363
[glasses clink]

632
00:29:16.450 --> 00:29:19.583
Getting to spend all
this time with Liana?

633
00:29:19.670 --> 00:29:21.542
Wouldn't change
it for the world.

634
00:29:21.629 --> 00:29:24.066
I am a changed man. Ruth.

635
00:29:24.153 --> 00:29:26.634
And if the town needs
its wartime general back?

636
00:29:26.721 --> 00:29:30.246
They already have theirs.

637
00:29:30.333 --> 00:29:32.727
The people elected you. Ruth.

638
00:29:32.858 --> 00:29:35.730
And there is not a better
person to lead them right now.

639
00:29:35.817 --> 00:29:38.733
<i>[soft upbeat music]</i>

640
00:29:38.820 --> 00:29:41.083
<i>♪ ♪</i>

641
00:29:41.170 --> 00:29:42.737
All right. I'm going
to go talk to Alex.

642
00:29:42.824 --> 00:29:45.609
see if she can tell
us where Boki's at.

643
00:29:45.784 --> 00:29:46.445
<i>♪ ♪</i>

644
00:30:03.323 --> 00:30:05.586
[door opens]

645
00:30:05.673 --> 00:30:08.371
[whispering] Hey. Sam. Hey.

646
00:30:08.458 --> 00:30:09.760
[whispering] Oh.
Sorry. I'm on patrol.

647
00:30:09.764 --> 00:30:10.500
Just checking in.
Did I wake Liana?

648
00:30:10.504 --> 00:30:11.810
It's OK.

649
00:30:11.897 --> 00:30:13.550
I was about to wake her anyway.

650
00:30:13.637 --> 00:30:15.244
No. no. no. you know rule
six of being a parent

651
00:30:15.248 --> 00:30:16.858
is never wake a sleeping kid.

652
00:30:16.945 --> 00:30:19.165
Yeah. but I gotta go up
the mountain to see Oz.

653
00:30:19.252 --> 00:30:20.775
I have to drop her with Andre.

654
00:30:20.862 --> 00:30:22.951
No. no. no. Let her
sleep. I'll watch her.

655
00:30:23.038 --> 00:30:25.388
Uh. that's OK. Don't
worry about it.

656
00:30:25.475 --> 00:30:27.390
Please. I'd be thrilled.

657
00:30:27.477 --> 00:30:29.127
Do you know how much I
missed this stage with Carly?

658
00:30:29.131 --> 00:30:32.439
Back before back tattoos became
the topic of conversation?

659
00:30:32.526 --> 00:30:34.702
You sure? I won't
be gone long.

660
00:30:34.789 --> 00:30:36.399
Please let me watch her. Go.

661
00:30:36.486 --> 00:30:38.767
- [whispering] Thanks. Sam.
- [whispering] Right. see you.

662
00:30:43.667 --> 00:30:44.973
[door opens]

663
00:30:45.060 --> 00:30:46.192
[knocks on door frame]

664
00:30:46.279 --> 00:30:47.628
Hello?

665
00:30:47.715 --> 00:30:49.021
Hey. [Alex clears throat]

666
00:30:49.108 --> 00:30:52.241
Missed you at the
meeting last night.

667
00:30:52.328 --> 00:30:55.070
And the last three before that.

668
00:30:55.157 --> 00:30:56.502
I don't have time
to play card games

669
00:30:56.506 --> 00:30:57.943
with you guys right now.

670
00:30:58.030 --> 00:31:00.467
[chuckles] Ouch.
officially offended.

671
00:31:00.554 --> 00:31:02.425
I'm just busy. OK?

672
00:31:02.512 --> 00:31:05.211
Melanie said that big minds
should solve big problems.

673
00:31:05.298 --> 00:31:08.997
Mm. so your pet bird qualifies
as a big problem now?

674
00:31:09.084 --> 00:31:11.043
[chuckles] First of all.

675
00:31:11.130 --> 00:31:13.480
Mr. Sprinkles is a dedicated
scientific collaborator.

676
00:31:13.567 --> 00:31:15.177
Second of all. how do
you know about him?

677
00:31:15.264 --> 00:31:16.309
You saw Boki?

678
00:31:16.396 --> 00:31:18.267
No. I wish.

679
00:31:18.354 --> 00:31:19.961
We could have used him today
to go check on the far relay.

680
00:31:19.965 --> 00:31:21.314
but you sent him on an errand.

681
00:31:21.401 --> 00:31:24.447
So when will he be back?

682
00:31:24.534 --> 00:31:25.622
Later tonight.

683
00:31:25.709 --> 00:31:27.276
Also. it's not an errand.

684
00:31:27.363 --> 00:31:28.887
He's going to the
edge of the pocket

685
00:31:29.017 --> 00:31:30.540
to get me data on
magnetic fields.

686
00:31:30.627 --> 00:31:33.935
barometric pressure.
seismographic readings.

687
00:31:34.066 --> 00:31:38.157
I have no idea what
you're talking about.

688
00:31:38.287 --> 00:31:39.680
We're having earthquakes.

689
00:31:39.767 --> 00:31:41.334
We've been having them.

690
00:31:41.421 --> 00:31:42.857
They're small and
they're sporadic.

691
00:31:42.944 --> 00:31:45.425
but they're real and
they're concerning.

692
00:31:45.512 --> 00:31:47.423
And I'm trying to figure out
if the atmospheric erosion

693
00:31:47.427 --> 00:31:48.994
is a corollary of the quakes.

694
00:31:49.081 --> 00:31:51.953
<i>[somber suspenseful music]</i>

695
00:31:52.040 --> 00:31:53.955
There's something that's
missing in the field.

696
00:31:54.042 --> 00:31:57.741
There's something that
doesn't make sense.

697
00:31:57.828 --> 00:32:00.657
Yeah. there's a lot
of that going around.

698
00:32:00.744 --> 00:32:03.660
[wind howling]

699
00:32:03.834 --> 00:32:04.495
<i>♪ ♪</i>

700
00:32:19.415 --> 00:32:23.245
[wings flapping]

701
00:32:23.332 --> 00:32:23.993
<i>♪ ♪</i>

702
00:32:28.816 --> 00:32:31.819
[pigeon cooing]

703
00:32:31.906 --> 00:32:33.647
<i>♪ ♪</i>

704
00:32:33.734 --> 00:32:36.389
[mechanical whirring]

705
00:32:36.476 --> 00:32:40.175
<i>♪ ♪</i>

706
00:32:40.262 --> 00:32:42.569
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

707
00:32:42.656 --> 00:32:44.353
[gasps softly]

708
00:32:44.440 --> 00:32:45.101
<i>♪ ♪</i>

709
00:33:00.717 --> 00:33:03.416
[screeching]

710
00:33:06.767 --> 00:33:09.770
[air hissing]

711
00:33:33.663 --> 00:33:36.144
Audrey?

712
00:33:36.231 --> 00:33:39.626
Audrey. what happened to you?

713
00:33:39.713 --> 00:33:41.715
[softly] They're coming.

714
00:33:41.889 --> 00:33:43.891
<i>♪ ♪</i>

715
00:33:44.022 --> 00:33:46.633
Audrey!

716
00:33:50.767 --> 00:33:53.422
<i>[soft suspenseful music]</i>

717
00:33:53.509 --> 00:33:57.209
<i>♪ ♪</i>

718
00:33:57.296 --> 00:33:59.298
[heavy breathing]

719
00:33:59.385 --> 00:34:04.042
<i>♪ ♪</i>

720
00:34:04.129 --> 00:34:05.478
Whoa. Oz. it's me.

721
00:34:05.565 --> 00:34:08.350
It's just me.

722
00:34:08.481 --> 00:34:09.917
Sorry.

723
00:34:10.048 --> 00:34:11.008
Can you just get inside?

724
00:34:11.049 --> 00:34:12.615
What's wrong?

725
00:34:12.702 --> 00:34:14.443
Sorry. I just thought
you were someone else.

726
00:34:15.836 --> 00:34:18.273
Who?

727
00:34:18.360 --> 00:34:20.319
You wouldn't believe
me if I told you.

728
00:34:23.539 --> 00:34:25.628
Those are a mess. We need
to take care of them.

729
00:34:29.328 --> 00:34:31.199
You came all the way
up here just for me?

730
00:34:34.028 --> 00:34:35.377
What?

731
00:34:35.464 --> 00:34:37.597
Why would you do that?

732
00:34:37.684 --> 00:34:42.036
Maybe because I
know what it's like

733
00:34:42.123 --> 00:34:46.214
to be an outsider. to
be constantly misjudged.

734
00:34:50.610 --> 00:34:53.134
Know what it feels like
to be so consumed by fear

735
00:34:53.221 --> 00:34:55.963
and just basic survival
that you forget

736
00:34:56.094 --> 00:34:58.444
what you're supposed
to be living for.

737
00:34:58.531 --> 00:35:01.447
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

738
00:35:01.577 --> 00:35:04.667
I can't live down there
in the bloody train.

739
00:35:04.754 --> 00:35:07.496
No one's asking you to.

740
00:35:07.583 --> 00:35:09.890
Just tell me what happened.

741
00:35:09.977 --> 00:35:11.544
We stopped moving.

742
00:35:11.674 --> 00:35:12.976
Yeah. that's a good
thing. isn't it?

743
00:35:12.980 --> 00:35:14.416
When you stop moving.

744
00:35:14.503 --> 00:35:17.724
the past catches up.
piles on top of you.

745
00:35:17.811 --> 00:35:19.856
So climb out from under it.

746
00:35:19.943 --> 00:35:23.338
- Ah.
- Sorry.

747
00:35:23.425 --> 00:35:25.558
When we're done
here. come with me.

748
00:35:25.645 --> 00:35:27.077
People are gathering
at the town hall

749
00:35:27.081 --> 00:35:28.561
to talk about
Snowpiercer's return.

750
00:35:28.648 --> 00:35:32.434
They're not coming back. Ever.

751
00:35:32.608 --> 00:35:35.698
<i>♪ ♪</i>

752
00:35:35.785 --> 00:35:39.659
Snowpiercer's gone.

753
00:35:39.746 --> 00:35:41.487
They're all dead.

754
00:35:41.574 --> 00:35:44.620
<i>[ominous music]</i>

755
00:35:44.794 --> 00:35:46.666
<i>♪ ♪</i>

756
00:35:46.796 --> 00:35:48.581
[indistinct chatter]

757
00:35:48.668 --> 00:35:50.191
All right. Thanks. everyone.

758
00:35:50.322 --> 00:35:51.845
<i>Has Snowpiercer answered back?</i>

759
00:35:51.932 --> 00:35:54.326
Thank you all for coming. I
know you all have questions.

760
00:35:54.456 --> 00:35:56.110
Questions about
some recent events.

761
00:35:56.241 --> 00:35:58.591
But before I take
those questions.

762
00:35:58.678 --> 00:36:00.027
I'd like to take a moment

763
00:36:00.114 --> 00:36:01.985
to express the
council's gratitude

764
00:36:02.072 --> 00:36:05.163
for your tireless efforts to
complete the trestle bridge.

765
00:36:05.293 --> 00:36:06.642
[applause] Really.

766
00:36:06.729 --> 00:36:09.645
Congratulations on
a job well done.

767
00:36:09.732 --> 00:36:13.649
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

768
00:36:13.780 --> 00:36:15.647
<i>It's been a long time since
we've seen our friends</i>

769
00:36:15.651 --> 00:36:16.783
<i>on Snowpiercer. hasn't it?</i>

770
00:36:16.957 --> 00:36:18.306
<i>♪ ♪</i>

771
00:36:18.393 --> 00:36:19.673
<i>Well. the day is
fast approaching</i>

772
00:36:19.786 --> 00:36:21.527
<i>when we get to see them again.</i>

773
00:36:21.614 --> 00:36:24.921
<i>to reunite. hug our
friends. and show them that</i>

774
00:36:25.008 --> 00:36:27.794
the risks we took coming
here were worth it.

775
00:36:27.881 --> 00:36:30.013
[applause]

776
00:36:30.100 --> 00:36:31.711
John. you're not making sense.

777
00:36:31.841 --> 00:36:33.582
What voices?

778
00:36:33.713 --> 00:36:34.840
First. there were just
these whispers in the wind

779
00:36:34.844 --> 00:36:36.455
in the middle of the night.

780
00:36:36.542 --> 00:36:37.669
But if you listen.
you can hear them.

781
00:36:37.673 --> 00:36:39.458
Sound carries in the mountains.

782
00:36:39.545 --> 00:36:40.585
- and the drinking doesn't...
- No. no. it's not that.

783
00:36:40.589 --> 00:36:42.330
I'm not drunk. I'm not crazy.

784
00:36:42.417 --> 00:36:43.810
I was married to a psychopath.

785
00:36:43.897 --> 00:36:45.177
so I know what
crazy sounds like.

786
00:36:45.290 --> 00:36:46.983
- That's not this.
- Please. just calm down.

787
00:36:46.987 --> 00:36:48.902
Something happened
on that train.

788
00:36:48.989 --> 00:36:50.860
Something awful.

789
00:36:50.991 --> 00:36:53.385
I don't know who's
responsible for all of it.

790
00:36:53.472 --> 00:36:55.604
What are you
talking about? Who?

791
00:36:55.691 --> 00:36:57.650
<i>♪ ♪</i>

792
00:36:57.737 --> 00:37:00.000
It's LJ.

793
00:37:00.130 --> 00:37:03.699
She won't... she
won't leave me alone.

794
00:37:03.830 --> 00:37:05.005
Come. come with me.

795
00:37:05.092 --> 00:37:06.572
[zipper zips] <i>Come.</i>

796
00:37:06.746 --> 00:37:07.407
<i>♪ ♪</i>

797
00:37:12.621 --> 00:37:14.797
Now... now just...
just listen.

798
00:37:14.884 --> 00:37:17.800
[wind howling]

799
00:37:17.887 --> 00:37:22.022
<i>♪ ♪</i>

800
00:37:22.152 --> 00:37:25.025
Oz. I know how
destructive LJ was.

801
00:37:25.155 --> 00:37:27.462
Just... just please.
just be quiet.

802
00:37:27.636 --> 00:37:29.508
<i>♪ ♪</i>

803
00:37:29.595 --> 00:37:30.813
If Snowpiercer returns.

804
00:37:30.900 --> 00:37:32.293
you don't have to deal with her.

805
00:37:32.380 --> 00:37:34.020
They're not returning.
I've just told you!

806
00:37:34.034 --> 00:37:35.161
Oz I'm trying to help you.
but you need to calm down.

807
00:37:35.165 --> 00:37:36.906
No. You listen! Just listen!

808
00:37:37.037 --> 00:37:38.517
All is not forgiven.

809
00:37:38.647 --> 00:37:41.128
We're just as guilty
as they are. all of us.

810
00:37:41.215 --> 00:37:42.216
They're already here.

811
00:37:42.303 --> 00:37:43.435
They're haunting this place

812
00:37:43.522 --> 00:37:44.867
because we made it
and they didn't.

813
00:37:44.871 --> 00:37:45.824
I'm sorry. I have to go.

814
00:37:45.828 --> 00:37:48.091
<i>♪ ♪</i>

815
00:37:48.178 --> 00:37:50.572
- Sorry.
- Can you just wait?

816
00:37:50.659 --> 00:37:52.487
Zarah!

817
00:37:52.661 --> 00:37:53.967
<i>♪ ♪</i>

818
00:37:54.054 --> 00:37:55.185
Zarah!

819
00:37:55.273 --> 00:37:55.934
<i>♪ ♪</i>

820
00:38:00.974 --> 00:38:04.020
[indistinct chatter]

821
00:38:04.107 --> 00:38:06.196
See you brought the Aloha gear.

822
00:38:06.327 --> 00:38:07.937
I tried to give Ruth
a smile tonight.

823
00:38:08.024 --> 00:38:09.243
That's good.

824
00:38:09.330 --> 00:38:10.588
I kind of missed the Aloha Javi.

825
00:38:10.592 --> 00:38:12.028
He knew how to have fun.

826
00:38:12.115 --> 00:38:14.553
Well. so did
Alex. [door opens]

827
00:38:14.683 --> 00:38:16.511
- Did I?
<i>- Hey. we need some help here!</i>

828
00:38:16.598 --> 00:38:18.339
Can somebody make some
room? We need help!

829
00:38:18.426 --> 00:38:19.209
- Gotcha.
- Yeah.

830
00:38:19.297 --> 00:38:20.820
I gotcha.

831
00:38:20.907 --> 00:38:23.257
- Zarah?
- God!

832
00:38:23.344 --> 00:38:24.563
Dr. Headwood?

833
00:38:24.650 --> 00:38:26.042
<i>Yeah. it's Audrey.</i>

834
00:38:26.173 --> 00:38:27.344
<i>She showed up on a track scaler.</i>

835
00:38:27.348 --> 00:38:28.302
<i>She's in really bad shape.</i>

836
00:38:28.306 --> 00:38:29.916
All right. everybody.

837
00:38:30.003 --> 00:38:32.001
- We need the room. please.
- Go get her some water.

838
00:38:32.005 --> 00:38:33.176
<i>- Quick as you can. can you?</i>
- What happened to her skin?

839
00:38:33.180 --> 00:38:34.877
<i>I don't know. She
showed up like this.</i>

840
00:38:34.964 --> 00:38:36.139
<i>She said someone was coming.</i>

841
00:38:36.270 --> 00:38:38.751
- Audrey?
<i>- Dr. Headwood?</i>

842
00:38:38.838 --> 00:38:40.274
<i>Audrey.</i>

843
00:38:40.361 --> 00:38:42.407
<i>[tense music]</i>

844
00:38:42.494 --> 00:38:43.712
Oh. not this again.

845
00:38:43.799 --> 00:38:44.579
I thought you fixed the cable.

846
00:38:44.583 --> 00:38:46.106
I did.

847
00:38:46.193 --> 00:38:46.885
<i>Javi. Alex. get
the power back on.</i>

848
00:38:46.889 --> 00:38:48.848
Let's go.

849
00:38:48.935 --> 00:38:50.415
Hey. hey. hey. hey.

850
00:38:50.502 --> 00:38:54.027
The power. the relays.
someone is not coming.

851
00:38:54.114 --> 00:38:55.376
They are already here.

852
00:38:55.463 --> 00:38:56.812
They've been here.

853
00:38:56.899 --> 00:38:58.031
Who?

854
00:38:58.161 --> 00:38:59.598
Where... where is Zarah?

855
00:38:59.685 --> 00:39:01.030
Why isn't she... I
need to find Liana.

856
00:39:01.034 --> 00:39:02.122
Out of the way!

857
00:39:02.209 --> 00:39:04.342
Audrey?

858
00:39:04.429 --> 00:39:05.865
Excuse me. Excuse me.

859
00:39:05.952 --> 00:39:08.346
<i>♪ ♪</i>

860
00:39:08.476 --> 00:39:11.784
Can you say Roche?
Can you say Roche?

861
00:39:11.871 --> 00:39:13.525
Yes. hello.

862
00:39:13.612 --> 00:39:14.134
Can you say Roche?
[baby giggling]

863
00:39:14.221 --> 00:39:16.092
Yes.

864
00:39:16.179 --> 00:39:18.094
Hey. Doc Headwood.
How you been?

865
00:39:18.181 --> 00:39:20.053
- Evening.
- Oh. don't worry. doc.

866
00:39:20.140 --> 00:39:22.380
Everything's going to be OK.
Probably just a loose cable.

867
00:39:23.491 --> 00:39:26.015
- [baby crying]
- I'm very sorry. Mr. Roche.

868
00:39:26.102 --> 00:39:28.061
<i>♪ ♪</i>

869
00:39:28.148 --> 00:39:29.367
<i>- Layton!</i>
- Hey.

870
00:39:29.454 --> 00:39:31.412
Layton. I just saw...

871
00:39:31.499 --> 00:39:32.848
Yeah. a track scaler. I know.

872
00:39:32.935 --> 00:39:34.459
- Miss Audrey was inside.
- What?

873
00:39:34.546 --> 00:39:36.939
Yeah. she's in bad shape.

874
00:39:37.026 --> 00:39:38.459
I took her up to the town
hall. but she needs a doctor.

875
00:39:38.463 --> 00:39:40.025
No. no. no. no. Miss
Audrey? Just stop. Stop.

876
00:39:40.029 --> 00:39:41.509
One thing at a time.

877
00:39:41.596 --> 00:39:43.772
I didn't see a track
scaler. I saw a snow cat.

878
00:39:43.903 --> 00:39:45.426
- What?
<i>- Yes.</i>

879
00:39:45.557 --> 00:39:47.080
<i>On the other side
of the mountain.</i>

880
00:39:47.210 --> 00:39:48.294
It was a... a
transport or something.

881
00:39:48.298 --> 00:39:50.605
We haven't got one of those.

882
00:39:50.736 --> 00:39:52.912
Neither does Snowpiercer.

883
00:39:52.999 --> 00:39:55.871
<i>[tense dramatic music]</i>

884
00:39:55.958 --> 00:39:58.221
<i>♪ ♪</i>

885
00:39:58.308 --> 00:40:01.964
Zarah. where are you?

886
00:40:02.051 --> 00:40:02.835
<i>Zarah?</i>

887
00:40:02.965 --> 00:40:05.098
Layton.

888
00:40:05.185 --> 00:40:09.624
Oh. sh... hey. hey. Sam.

889
00:40:09.711 --> 00:40:11.583
<i>Sam. come on. buddy.</i>

890
00:40:11.670 --> 00:40:12.801
<i>He's got a pulse.</i>

891
00:40:12.888 --> 00:40:13.549
<i>♪ ♪</i>

892
00:40:25.510 --> 00:40:28.338
[wind howling]

893
00:40:28.426 --> 00:40:31.472
[baby crying]

894
00:40:32.908 --> 00:40:34.780
Liana?

895
00:40:34.910 --> 00:40:36.259
<i>[ominous music]</i>

896
00:40:36.346 --> 00:40:38.131
Liana.

897
00:40:38.218 --> 00:40:41.134
[baby crying]

898
00:40:41.308 --> 00:40:45.486
<i>♪ ♪</i>

899
00:40:45.573 --> 00:40:47.488
- Dr. Headwood?
- Zarah.

900
00:40:50.273 --> 00:40:51.666
Who is that with you?

901
00:40:51.753 --> 00:40:53.102
Remain calm.

902
00:40:53.189 --> 00:40:54.317
Everything's going
to be all right.

903
00:40:54.321 --> 00:40:56.323
Give me my daughter.

904
00:40:56.410 --> 00:40:58.456
<i>Zarah. stop. stop!</i>

905
00:40:58.586 --> 00:41:00.545
He is a friend.
Zarah. He's a friend.

906
00:41:00.632 --> 00:41:02.155
<i>[tense music]</i>

907
00:41:02.242 --> 00:41:03.809
Give me my daughter. Now!

908
00:41:03.896 --> 00:41:05.415
No. don't... don't...
don't... don't fight!

909
00:41:05.419 --> 00:41:06.198
Zarah. don't fight with him!

910
00:41:06.202 --> 00:41:07.552
Give her to me now!

911
00:41:07.639 --> 00:41:09.162
Get off of me.

912
00:41:09.249 --> 00:41:10.420
<i>Please. Zarah. I am
trying to help you.</i>

913
00:41:10.424 --> 00:41:11.290
<i>Zarah. don't fight with him.</i>

914
00:41:11.294 --> 00:41:12.470
Give me my daughter!

915
00:41:12.557 --> 00:41:13.797
Stop fighting with him. please.

916
00:41:13.862 --> 00:41:16.125
- Dr. Headwood!
- Please stop this.

917
00:41:16.212 --> 00:41:17.823
- Just stop.
- Get off of me!

918
00:41:17.910 --> 00:41:18.911
- Give her to me!
- Zarah!

919
00:41:18.998 --> 00:41:19.958
We stemmed the bleeding.

920
00:41:19.999 --> 00:41:21.653
but he never woke up.

921
00:41:21.740 --> 00:41:23.263
He needs help.

922
00:41:23.350 --> 00:41:24.960
God. How the hell did
this happen. Andre?

923
00:41:25.047 --> 00:41:28.224
Look. just get a nurse.
Go to the clinic.

924
00:41:28.355 --> 00:41:30.048
I'm going to round up
volunteers to search the hills.

925
00:41:30.052 --> 00:41:31.920
Josie's already up there.
I need everybody. Ruth.

926
00:41:31.924 --> 00:41:34.927
- I'll get her.
- Everybody.

927
00:41:35.014 --> 00:41:35.675
<i>♪ ♪</i>

928
00:42:03.433 --> 00:42:05.087
Zarah!

929
00:42:05.174 --> 00:42:05.835
<i>♪ ♪</i>

930
00:42:12.573 --> 00:42:16.011
Who's that?

931
00:42:16.098 --> 00:42:18.666
It's Bojan Boscovic.
You must come with me.

932
00:42:18.753 --> 00:42:19.928
Please. Hurry.

933
00:42:20.015 --> 00:42:21.364
Yeah.

934
00:42:21.539 --> 00:42:22.200
<i>♪ ♪</i>

935
00:42:33.463 --> 00:42:35.422
It's her back.

936
00:42:37.598 --> 00:42:39.948
I did not want to move her.

937
00:42:40.035 --> 00:42:41.994
Zarah?

938
00:42:42.081 --> 00:42:45.258
Zarah. Zarah. it's Josie.

939
00:42:45.345 --> 00:42:46.215
Can you hear me?

940
00:42:46.302 --> 00:42:47.826
[Zarah wheezes]

941
00:42:47.956 --> 00:42:49.784
- What?
- Hey.

942
00:42:49.871 --> 00:42:51.612
Liana.

943
00:42:51.699 --> 00:42:55.181
They took Liana.

944
00:42:55.268 --> 00:42:56.922
<i>Who took her? Liana.</i>

945
00:42:57.009 --> 00:42:59.315
[Zarah breathing hoarsely]

946
00:42:59.402 --> 00:43:02.275
[hoarsely] Headwood.

947
00:43:02.362 --> 00:43:04.103
<i>And a stranger.</i>

948
00:43:06.409 --> 00:43:09.195
Not one of us. Not one of us.

949
00:43:09.325 --> 00:43:11.197
<i>- OK.</i>
- Liana.

950
00:43:11.327 --> 00:43:13.895
Take care of Liana.

951
00:43:16.071 --> 00:43:19.597
We will.

952
00:43:19.684 --> 00:43:22.077
<i>[somber music]</i>

953
00:43:22.164 --> 00:43:23.557
[weakly] Josie's there.

954
00:43:23.644 --> 00:43:25.515
<i>Mm-hmm.</i>

955
00:43:25.603 --> 00:43:29.345
Can't feel anything.

956
00:43:29.432 --> 00:43:31.478
<i>♪ ♪</i>

957
00:43:31.565 --> 00:43:33.959
I'm right here.

958
00:43:34.133 --> 00:43:34.794
<i>♪ ♪</i>

959
00:43:52.151 --> 00:43:56.329
Everyone pan out.
Javi. you go east.

960
00:43:56.416 --> 00:43:58.762
Alex. you take the north hills.
They're out there somewhere.

961
00:43:58.766 --> 00:44:02.335
Layton.

962
00:44:02.422 --> 00:44:05.294
No. no. no. no. no. no.
no. no. no. no. no. no!

963
00:44:05.381 --> 00:44:06.731
Zarah! Zarah!

964
00:44:06.818 --> 00:44:07.945
She was at the
bottom of a cliff.

965
00:44:07.949 --> 00:44:10.125
She was almost gone
when we reached her.

966
00:44:10.212 --> 00:44:13.433
<i>♪ ♪</i>

967
00:44:13.520 --> 00:44:15.000
I'm sorry.

968
00:44:15.087 --> 00:44:15.748
<i>♪ ♪</i>

969
00:44:27.403 --> 00:44:31.277
Where's Liana?

970
00:44:31.364 --> 00:44:33.714
<i>I don't know.</i>

971
00:44:33.801 --> 00:44:35.411
Where is she?

972
00:44:35.498 --> 00:44:36.713
It was Headwood and a stranger.

973
00:44:36.717 --> 00:44:37.631
I don't know. Layton.

974
00:44:37.718 --> 00:44:41.548
I... Layton.

975
00:44:41.635 --> 00:44:43.332
<i>Layton. they... they've gone.</i>

976
00:44:43.463 --> 00:44:44.899
They had a vehicle.

977
00:44:45.030 --> 00:44:46.945
You'll die if you go out there.

978
00:44:47.075 --> 00:44:49.425
Listen to me. it's too late!

979
00:44:49.512 --> 00:44:52.777
It's too late. Layton.

980
00:44:52.864 --> 00:44:55.214
Layton. it's too late.

981
00:44:55.301 --> 00:44:58.217
<i>[somber music]</i>

982
00:44:58.391 --> 00:44:59.052
<i>♪ ♪</i>

983
00:45:24.330 --> 00:45:25.897
Layton.

984
00:45:26.071 --> 00:45:29.901
<i>♪ ♪</i>

985
00:45:29.988 --> 00:45:31.903
I'm going to find
who took Liana.

986
00:45:32.077 --> 00:45:35.384
<i>♪ ♪</i>

987
00:45:35.471 --> 00:45:39.693
And I'm going to kill him.

988
00:45:39.824 --> 00:45:41.956
Whatever it takes.

989
00:45:42.043 --> 00:45:44.611
<i>[tense dramatic music]</i>

990
00:45:44.698 --> 00:45:45.359
<i>♪ ♪</i>

991
00:46:25.870 --> 00:46:27.654
<i>Who are you guys?
What's going on?</i>

992
00:46:27.785 --> 00:46:29.395
<i>Put your guns down!</i>

993
00:46:29.482 --> 00:46:30.788
Admiral Anton Milius.

994
00:46:30.875 --> 00:46:32.398
International Peace
Keeping Forces.

995
00:46:32.485 --> 00:46:33.965
Survivors.

996
00:46:34.052 --> 00:46:35.488
<i>Everyone remain calm.</i>

997
00:46:35.575 --> 00:46:37.446
Everyone except you two.

998
00:46:37.533 --> 00:46:40.362
You're taking me
to Melanie Cavill.

999
00:46:40.449 --> 00:46:43.365
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

1000
00:46:43.539 --> 00:46:44.200
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1001
00:46:56.074 --> 00:46:57.423
♪

1002
00:46:57.553 --> 00:46:58.728
- Layton.
- Yeah.

1003
00:46:58.859 --> 00:47:00.034
They took the train.

1004
00:47:00.252 --> 00:47:04.212
♪

1005
00:47:04.343 --> 00:47:06.214
Attention! The new
passengers want you to know

1006
00:47:06.388 --> 00:47:08.148
that. uh. as long as
you do as you're told...

1007
00:47:08.216 --> 00:47:09.043
[Gunshot]

1008
00:47:09.174 --> 00:47:09.957
...all is well.

1009
00:47:10.131 --> 00:47:12.133
♪

1010
00:47:12.220 --> 00:47:14.222
The work we're doing is
going to save the world.

1011
00:47:14.396 --> 00:47:16.268
Gemini will not launch
until it's been proven.

1012
00:47:16.485 --> 00:47:18.487
♪

1013
00:47:18.574 --> 00:47:21.055
- Dada?
- Daddy's coming.

1014
00:47:21.186 --> 00:47:22.879
How long will it take to unhook
this and get it running again?

1015
00:47:22.883 --> 00:47:24.489
- Unhook what?
- We're going after Snowpiercer.

1016
00:47:24.493 --> 00:47:27.018
♪

1017
00:47:27.148 --> 00:47:30.064
The train goes nowhere
without its creator.

1018
00:47:30.151 --> 00:47:32.501
Ruth: If they take Big Alice.
we don't just lose New Eden.

1019
00:47:32.675 --> 00:47:33.435
We lose everything.

1020
00:47:33.546 --> 00:47:35.461
[Screaming]

1021
00:47:35.591 --> 00:47:37.811
The people of New Eden
are ready for any fight...

1022
00:47:37.942 --> 00:47:40.031
versus man. beast. or train.

1023
00:47:40.292 --> 00:47:42.860
♪

